HEADWORD: Leptiform
<hw>Lep"ti*form</hw> <pr>(-t⟦icr⟧*f⟦ocir⟧rm)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Leptus</ets> + <ets>-form</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Having a form somewhat like leptus; -- said of active insect larvae
having three pairs of legs. See <er>Larva</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

